<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="246">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:179084" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus depilis clarior Santschi" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus depilis clarior Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="affinis" subSpecies="depilis" variety="clarior">Dorylus affinis Shuck, stirps depilis Em. var. clarior</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="variety">n. var.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="246">
[[ male ]]. Differe de 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:179285" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus affinis depilis Emery" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus affinis depilis Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="affinis" subSpecies="depilis">depilis</taxonomicName>
par sa couleur jaune terne ou jaune roussatre (comme chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:28783" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus affinis Shuckard" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus affinis Shuckard" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">affinis</taxonomicName>
i. sp., tandis que 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:179285" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus affinis depilis Emery" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus affinis depilis Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="affinis" subSpecies="depilis">depilis</taxonomicName>
est bien plus fonce). Tete brune, noiratre, ailes anterieures longues de 16 mm. (15 mm. chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:28783" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus affinis Shuckard" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus affinis Shuckard" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="affinis">affinis</taxonomicName>
); pilosite comme chez 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:179285" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus affinis depilis Emery" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus affinis depilis Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="affinis" subSpecies="depilis">depilis</taxonomicName>
Em.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="246">Zambezie (Durand 1889, Museum de Paris). — Congo belge: Oubanghi (Rev. P. Augustin), 1 [[ male ]].</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="246">
Des exemplaires de Fernando-Po font passage a la couleur plus sombre de 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:179285" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Dorylus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dorylus affinis depilis Emery" lsidName-HNS="Dorylus affinis depilis Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="affinis" subSpecies="depilis">depilis</taxonomicName>
. Chez D. affinis 
<taxonomicName authority="Santschi" authorityName="Santschi" rank="variety" variety="ugandensis">var. ugandensis Santschi</taxonomicName>
, la tete est rougeatre et plus transversale, le 2 ° article du funicule plus court.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
